2
00:00:54,490 --> 00:00:56,258
(This drama is fiction and people, places, organizations,)

3
00:00:56,259 --> 00:00:58,030
(incidents, groups, and nations are not based on reality.)

4
00:00:58,759 --> 00:01:00,060
Mr. Chairman is here.

5
00:01:14,049 --> 00:01:15,150
Welcome.

6
00:01:15,510 --> 00:01:16,780
Congratulations, sir.

7
00:01:17,980 --> 00:01:19,120
Congratulations.

8
00:01:19,920 --> 00:01:21,090
Congratulations.

9
00:01:23,219 --> 00:01:24,390
Congratulations.

10
00:01:24,790 --> 00:01:26,719
- Congratulations. - Hello.

11
00:01:27,959 --> 00:01:29,329
- Congratulations, sir. - Congratulations, sir.

12
00:01:51,650 --> 00:01:54,319
The founder of Soonyang.

13
00:01:55,819 --> 00:01:58,319
It's him. Chairman Jin Yang Cheol.

14
00:02:00,659 --> 00:02:03,359
This is a dream. It can't be reality.

15
00:02:07,200 --> 00:02:08,930
He died 20 years ago.

16
00:02:16,340 --> 00:02:17,639
How could this be?

17
00:02:32,719 --> 00:02:33,759
Do Jun.

18
00:02:35,389 --> 00:02:36,729
Forgive me, Father.

19
00:02:51,009 --> 00:02:55,409
Do Jun. You must watch your manners when you're around Grandfather.

20
00:02:55,849 --> 00:02:58,719
He's young. It happens when you're overwhelmed.

21
00:02:59,419 --> 00:03:02,590
I'll watch Do Jun. You can go on ahead.

22
00:03:02,789 --> 00:03:03,789
Okay, then.

23
00:03:04,460 --> 00:03:05,759
You sweet boy.

24
00:03:09,860 --> 00:03:12,530
That's what your grandfather is like.

25
00:03:12,860 --> 00:03:15,330
Nothing about his life is fun.

26
00:03:15,930 --> 00:03:18,839
Would thorns break out on his hand...

27
00:03:18,840 --> 00:03:21,509
if he were to just stroke your head?

28
00:03:22,310 --> 00:03:25,580
Do Jun. Come with Grandma.

29
00:03:26,979 --> 00:03:29,879
- "Grandma?" - Yes, sweetie.

30
00:03:33,379 --> 00:03:34,449
Who...

31
00:03:35,789 --> 00:03:37,159
Who am I?

32
00:03:38,060 --> 00:03:39,319
You're so silly.

33
00:03:39,590 --> 00:03:43,159
What kind of question is that? You are Jin Do Jun,

34
00:03:43,530 --> 00:03:45,560
the youngest grandchild of the Soonyang family.

35
00:03:54,740 --> 00:03:57,110
(The 24th Trade Day Business Medal Reward Ceremony)

36
00:03:58,409 --> 00:04:02,509
It's the year 1987?

37
00:04:04,620 --> 00:04:08,020
I'm a member of Chairman Jin Yang Cheol's family?

38
00:04:09,520 --> 00:04:10,659
The youngest?

39
00:04:11,560 --> 00:04:12,860
This can't be.

40
00:04:15,330 --> 00:04:17,398
(The 24th Seoul Olympic Games)

41
00:04:17,399 --> 00:04:21,500
(Reborn Rich)

42
00:04:21,670 --> 00:04:24,199
(Episode 2)

43
00:04:27,170 --> 00:04:30,009
Hyeong Jun, Do Jun, it's your first visit, isn't it?

44
00:04:32,139 --> 00:04:33,709
This is Grandpa's place.

45
00:04:33,910 --> 00:04:36,449
Whoa. Is this the main entrance?

46
00:04:37,019 --> 00:04:38,518
It's massive.

47
00:04:38,519 --> 00:04:39,680
It's just the same.

48
00:04:40,389 --> 00:04:44,259
Jeongsimjae, the Soonyang residence that was theirs for generations.

49
00:04:45,959 --> 00:04:47,560
A monk well-versed in geomancy...

50
00:04:48,029 --> 00:04:50,930
picked out the auspicious spot for a home and told Chairman Jin...

51
00:04:52,259 --> 00:04:56,029
as long as they were good at heart, money would never dry up.

52
00:04:57,699 --> 00:04:59,199
The name "Jeongsimjae..."

53
00:05:00,199 --> 00:05:02,170
literally means "rightful heart."

54
00:05:21,829 --> 00:05:23,959
Wow, this is amazing.

55
00:05:26,399 --> 00:05:29,230
One, two, three, four, five.

56
00:05:29,470 --> 00:05:32,040
Gosh. How many rooms are there?

57
00:05:32,199 --> 00:05:33,339
Thirteen.

58
00:05:34,939 --> 00:05:37,310
What? How do you know that?

59
00:05:37,779 --> 00:05:40,139
Have you been here without me?

60
00:05:41,009 --> 00:05:42,379
Don't be silly.

61
00:05:43,279 --> 00:05:45,778
Hyeong Jun, you promised Mom.

62
00:05:45,779 --> 00:05:47,319
That you'll be a good boy today.

63
00:05:47,990 --> 00:05:48,990
Yes.

64
00:05:50,319 --> 00:05:51,519
Do Jun, you too.

65
00:05:53,060 --> 00:05:54,360
Don't get too nervous.

66
00:05:54,589 --> 00:05:57,029
It looks like you're nervous.

67
00:05:58,259 --> 00:05:59,300
What?

68
00:06:01,029 --> 00:06:04,540
Let's go. Grandma and Grandpa will be waiting.

69
00:06:06,769 --> 00:06:07,810
Come along.

70
00:06:19,120 --> 00:06:23,388
Bells toll and flowers are in bloom

71
00:06:23,389 --> 00:06:27,628
Birds sing and people smile

72
00:06:27,629 --> 00:06:31,958
I miss you, my love

73
00:06:31,959 --> 00:06:35,500
Please do not leave my side

74
00:06:35,730 --> 00:06:39,600
Where we first met and fell in love

75
00:06:39,939 --> 00:06:43,980
The sweet roads I gave my heart to

76
00:06:44,240 --> 00:06:48,349
In beautiful Seoul

77
00:06:48,350 --> 00:06:53,019
I want to live in Seoul

78
00:07:08,829 --> 00:07:12,239
However busy you are, the meat and fish cannot be cold.

79
00:07:12,240 --> 00:07:15,240
Reheat and reserve every now and then.

80
00:07:20,779 --> 00:07:23,279
- Do not scrimp on the salt. - I understand.

81
00:07:23,480 --> 00:07:26,378
People these days eat less salt to stay healthy,

82
00:07:26,379 --> 00:07:28,350
but food must be seasoned enough.

83
00:07:28,550 --> 00:07:30,689
Don't worry about that, Mother.

84
00:07:30,920 --> 00:07:33,019
Your first daughter-in-law has it under control.

85
00:07:33,959 --> 00:07:37,458
I'll teach my sister-in-law how we do things.

86
00:07:37,459 --> 00:07:38,759
Don't worry, okay?

87
00:07:40,970 --> 00:07:43,299
My husband handpicked...

88
00:07:43,300 --> 00:07:46,698
Soonyang Hotel's best cooks and waiting staff.

89
00:07:46,699 --> 00:07:49,569
Don't worry about anything and stay by Father's side.

90
00:07:49,639 --> 00:07:51,110
You're the guest of honor.

91
00:07:51,379 --> 00:07:55,310
It's your father-in-law's birthday, and he's the one who won the medal.

92
00:07:55,410 --> 00:07:56,948
How am I the guest of honor?

93
00:07:56,949 --> 00:07:58,019
Don't say that.

94
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:03,389
Soonyang owes its immense growth to you, Mother.

95
00:08:03,620 --> 00:08:06,259
Who doesn't know that?

96
00:08:06,589 --> 00:08:09,730
That's such a sweet way of telling me to stop nagging...

97
00:08:09,889 --> 00:08:11,360
and get out of the kitchen.

98
00:08:13,730 --> 00:08:15,100
Hello, Hae In.

99
00:08:18,339 --> 00:08:21,569
What should I do, Mother?

100
00:08:22,370 --> 00:08:24,709
Don't you even think of doing anything.

101
00:08:25,209 --> 00:08:27,649
Stay with Yoon Ki and the boys.

102
00:08:30,879 --> 00:08:33,219
- Mother, leave it to us. - Okay.

103
00:08:33,220 --> 00:08:34,549
Go on.

104
00:08:36,289 --> 00:08:37,959
Do you want me...

105
00:08:37,960 --> 00:08:40,158
- to prepare the fruit? - Mr. Ko, get the fruit.

106
00:08:40,159 --> 00:08:41,389
Yes, ma'am.

107
00:08:42,360 --> 00:08:43,730
They're gutsy.

108
00:08:44,299 --> 00:08:47,298
He cut contact to marry a woman his parents disapproved of.

109
00:08:47,299 --> 00:08:49,429
They then showed up after ten years...

110
00:08:49,500 --> 00:08:51,870
to laugh and smile and enjoy having a family.

111
00:08:53,370 --> 00:08:56,009
I'm incapable of putting on such an act.

112
00:08:56,240 --> 00:08:58,080
She's not like us at all.

113
00:08:59,110 --> 00:09:00,909
She was an actress.

114
00:09:01,480 --> 00:09:03,450
She doesn't suit this family.

115
00:09:03,879 --> 00:09:05,350
She belongs on stage.

116
00:09:06,379 --> 00:09:07,450
Right?

117
00:09:10,720 --> 00:09:13,190
Are you being bullies now because you weren't in school?

118
00:09:13,559 --> 00:09:16,960
You have way too many wrinkles by your eyes.

119
00:09:17,830 --> 00:09:19,659
- Ms. Ye Jun. - What are you doing?

120
00:09:21,100 --> 00:09:23,500
When so many people are present?

121
00:09:25,039 --> 00:09:26,240
Ms. Lee.

122
00:09:29,269 --> 00:09:31,509
Don't try to play a daughter-in-law...

123
00:09:32,039 --> 00:09:33,210
and stick to what you did.

124
00:09:33,779 --> 00:09:36,779
Stand still like a portrait and smile prettily.

125
00:09:38,679 --> 00:09:39,779
You're good at that.

126
00:09:55,629 --> 00:09:56,899
Happy birthday, sir.

127
00:09:58,570 --> 00:09:59,639
Happy birthday, sir.

128
00:10:00,669 --> 00:10:01,809
Let's have a drink.

129
00:10:02,440 --> 00:10:04,809
- Happy birthday. - Happy birthday, sir.

130
00:10:10,210 --> 00:10:11,720
He studied in Tokyo...

131
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:15,190
and works as a master at a sushi restaurant in Ginza.

132
00:10:16,250 --> 00:10:19,058
The Japanese refused to let him go,

133
00:10:19,059 --> 00:10:21,388
but I literally abducted him and got him...

134
00:10:21,389 --> 00:10:24,330
on an early flight so he could cater to you today.

135
00:10:25,700 --> 00:10:26,759
It's good, isn't it?

136
00:10:27,259 --> 00:10:28,330
Yes.

137
00:10:28,429 --> 00:10:29,529
I knew it.

138
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:33,269
Domestic goods still can't compare to Japanese.

139
00:10:37,110 --> 00:10:38,139
How many?

140
00:10:39,779 --> 00:10:42,350
Grains of rice. How many are there?

141
00:10:42,750 --> 00:10:45,949
The ideal weight of fish and rice is 15g...

142
00:10:45,950 --> 00:10:46,980
So how many?

143
00:10:48,620 --> 00:10:51,320
- I apologize, sir. - There are 320.

144
00:10:52,519 --> 00:10:54,230
A trained sushi master...

145
00:10:55,289 --> 00:10:58,960
usually picks up 320 grains of rice to make one piece.

146
00:10:59,399 --> 00:11:02,100
That many might be appropriate for lunch,

147
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:05,899
but on a day like this, or when served with alcohol,

148
00:11:07,240 --> 00:11:09,769
use just 280 grains of rice, okay?

149
00:11:11,309 --> 00:11:12,379
So it's not too filling.

150
00:11:13,210 --> 00:11:14,480
I'll do that, sir.

151
00:11:19,779 --> 00:11:21,620
Cheongwadae sent a messenger, sir.

152
00:11:25,360 --> 00:11:27,429
- The Blue House? - Yes.

153
00:11:41,710 --> 00:11:42,740
Sir.

154
00:11:42,970 --> 00:11:44,409
- Happy birthday. - Happy birthday.

155
00:11:44,509 --> 00:11:46,579
Thank you. Eat your fill.

156
00:11:46,580 --> 00:11:47,649
- Thank you. - Thank you.

157
00:11:51,250 --> 00:11:54,549
Father. How did you know the number of rice grains?

158
00:11:56,090 --> 00:11:58,960
Is there a Japanese restaurant in Soonyang Hotel, yes or no?

159
00:11:59,289 --> 00:12:00,489
Of course...

160
00:12:00,490 --> 00:12:02,789
There. Must I say more?

161
00:12:06,929 --> 00:12:08,029
Hey, you.

162
00:12:08,529 --> 00:12:12,000
Deputy CEO of Soonyang Electronics. Tell me.

163
00:12:12,840 --> 00:12:14,639
What is this year's sales?

164
00:12:15,340 --> 00:12:16,969
It's 2.3 billion dollars.

165
00:12:16,970 --> 00:12:19,008
- Up by 15 percent... - And the Japanese?

166
00:12:19,009 --> 00:12:22,509
H made 26.5 billion dollars, and T made 20 billion dollars.

167
00:12:23,049 --> 00:12:24,678
Both more than ten times we did.

168
00:12:24,679 --> 00:12:27,049
Our deputy CEO is right, then.

169
00:12:27,750 --> 00:12:29,889
We still can't compare to the Japanese.

170
00:12:32,159 --> 00:12:33,159
Is that true?

171
00:12:33,289 --> 00:12:35,129
Still, we're number one in our country.

172
00:12:35,590 --> 00:12:37,288
We never lost...

173
00:12:37,289 --> 00:12:40,058
the top spot in Korea in the white goods market.

174
00:12:40,059 --> 00:12:42,370
The top spot in Korea.

175
00:12:43,700 --> 00:12:44,740
The top spot in Korea?

176
00:12:46,370 --> 00:12:48,139
Are you competing in a national competition?

177
00:12:54,950 --> 00:12:56,009
Father.

178
00:12:57,750 --> 00:12:59,720
Yoon Ki wishes to say hello.

179
00:13:04,019 --> 00:13:06,889
Congratulations on winning a medal and happy birthday, Father.

180
00:13:08,389 --> 00:13:11,929
He opened a film distribution company.

181
00:13:12,059 --> 00:13:14,700
His first movie will be shown this year.

182
00:13:15,000 --> 00:13:16,869
Aren't you proud of him?

183
00:13:16,870 --> 00:13:19,039
He did it all without your help.

184
00:13:19,970 --> 00:13:22,509
He'll do well. He's your son.

185
00:13:23,740 --> 00:13:27,850
He said he'll visit every weekend like the others.

186
00:13:28,509 --> 00:13:29,679
If you permit it.

187
00:13:30,279 --> 00:13:34,590
He did a great job raising both boys.

188
00:13:34,789 --> 00:13:37,860
Hyeong Jun, Do Jun, come and meet your grandfather.

189
00:13:39,860 --> 00:13:40,889
Bow.

190
00:13:41,529 --> 00:13:42,789
Yes, Father.

191
00:13:43,190 --> 00:13:44,928
Don't be so angry with him.

192
00:13:44,929 --> 00:13:46,429
Do movies make money, mister?

193
00:13:48,129 --> 00:13:49,829
Something more valuable than money...

194
00:13:49,830 --> 00:13:51,370
Will it help Soonyang?

195
00:13:52,100 --> 00:13:53,839
- Father. - It makes no money...

196
00:13:53,840 --> 00:13:55,309
and won't help Soonyang.

197
00:13:56,610 --> 00:13:58,110
Why are you my son?

198
00:14:01,110 --> 00:14:03,179
- Honey. - Guests are leaving.

199
00:14:04,980 --> 00:14:06,049
Throw salt after them.

200
00:14:11,789 --> 00:14:13,320
It really is a party.

201
00:14:13,590 --> 00:14:15,730
There are beggars everywhere.

202
00:14:19,799 --> 00:14:22,330
He doesn't mean what he says.

203
00:14:27,299 --> 00:14:29,669
Yoon Ki, you know what your father's like.

204
00:14:30,740 --> 00:14:33,009
Don't take it to heart, okay?

205
00:14:34,179 --> 00:14:36,308
Yes. Leave it at that today.

206
00:14:36,309 --> 00:14:37,779
Let's take it slowly.

207
00:14:38,750 --> 00:14:39,750
Let's go and eat.

208
00:14:39,879 --> 00:14:41,350
You eat lots.

209
00:14:44,519 --> 00:14:46,289
He married against his parents' will,

210
00:14:46,820 --> 00:14:49,558
so 4-0's right to succession was revoked.

211
00:14:49,559 --> 00:14:50,690
Hello.

212
00:14:51,399 --> 00:14:54,029
That's exactly what I know.

213
00:15:13,649 --> 00:15:14,720
But...

214
00:15:20,289 --> 00:15:21,389
I'm missing.

215
00:15:23,789 --> 00:15:26,899
I know all there is to know about Soonyang's Jin family.

216
00:15:27,529 --> 00:15:28,600
But...

217
00:15:28,769 --> 00:15:30,730
(Late Jin Yang Cheol, Late Lee Pil Ok)

218
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:33,370
(Jin Yoon Ki, Lee Hae In, Jin Hyeong Jun)

219
00:15:36,840 --> 00:15:40,409
I have no information on 4-2 Jin Do Jun.

220
00:15:42,549 --> 00:15:43,580
Why...

221
00:15:44,049 --> 00:15:48,090
is my mind blank when it comes to 4-2 Jin Do Jun?

222
00:15:50,350 --> 00:15:51,360
Why is that?

223
00:15:58,700 --> 00:16:00,599
You know, sir,

224
00:16:00,600 --> 00:16:03,100
how the great 6.29 Declaration came to be.

225
00:16:03,700 --> 00:16:08,610
It was all thanks to the President's concern and thoughtfulness.

226
00:16:10,039 --> 00:16:11,639
History will record him...

227
00:16:11,840 --> 00:16:14,850
as the father of democracy in our land.

228
00:16:18,220 --> 00:16:19,279
Try the tea.

229
00:16:20,750 --> 00:16:21,820
It smells lovely.

230
00:16:26,990 --> 00:16:28,090
In the next administration,

231
00:16:29,789 --> 00:16:32,860
shouldn't the average man take the lead role?

232
00:16:34,929 --> 00:16:36,830
History is marching on,

233
00:16:37,429 --> 00:16:39,039
and Soonyang should join the flow.

234
00:16:41,409 --> 00:16:44,840
The President wishes to give you an opportunity.

235
00:16:53,450 --> 00:16:54,620
Mr. Lee.

236
00:16:55,220 --> 00:16:56,220
Yes, sir.

237
00:16:58,190 --> 00:16:59,490
Were you aware?

238
00:17:01,230 --> 00:17:05,099
This gentleman from the Blue House knew.

239
00:17:12,539 --> 00:17:15,309
This medal you see here.

240
00:17:17,069 --> 00:17:18,240
The payment is deferred.

241
00:17:21,009 --> 00:17:22,650
He's here to collect.

242
00:17:26,079 --> 00:17:27,079
So,

243
00:17:30,789 --> 00:17:33,019
how much do you want for it?

244
00:17:48,339 --> 00:17:53,210
Your window just won't open

245
00:17:54,079 --> 00:17:58,480
I'll knock on it with the moonlight of love

246
00:18:00,920 --> 00:18:01,920
Jeez...

247
00:18:14,769 --> 00:18:19,299
Oh, my love

248
00:18:19,640 --> 00:18:22,909
Open the window to let in the breeze

249
00:18:22,910 --> 00:18:23,910
Shoot.

250
00:18:44,630 --> 00:18:46,099
Vice-Chairman Jin Seong Jun?

251
00:18:54,470 --> 00:18:56,509
It's obvious what movies make money.

252
00:18:57,039 --> 00:18:59,139
- Hong Kongers shooting guns. - "A Better Tomorrow?"

253
00:18:59,140 --> 00:19:01,380
- Or Americans going to war. - "Platoon."

254
00:19:02,079 --> 00:19:03,509
So what kind of movie are you making?

255
00:19:04,309 --> 00:19:06,579
It's about the French people praying.

256
00:19:06,980 --> 00:19:08,519
It's called "Under the Sun of Satan."

257
00:19:08,990 --> 00:19:11,819
I thought you wanted to make a movie, not build a hotel.

258
00:19:12,460 --> 00:19:13,920
Do you want to make everyone fall asleep?

259
00:19:15,859 --> 00:19:18,160
Dad! Do Jun is in trouble.

260
00:19:18,630 --> 00:19:19,660
He's upstairs now.

261
00:19:30,640 --> 00:19:33,309
You broke this vase. Okay, kiddo?

262
00:19:34,779 --> 00:19:36,710
We're the only ones in this room right now.

263
00:19:37,180 --> 00:19:40,779
No matter what you say, everyone will believe me.

264
00:19:42,390 --> 00:19:45,289
Why? Because I'm the rightful heir to the throne,

265
00:19:45,619 --> 00:19:47,460
and Grandpa will side with me no matter what.

266
00:20:00,039 --> 00:20:01,099
Did you just scoff?

267
00:20:01,440 --> 00:20:03,609
You were a real mess even when you were young.

268
00:20:04,809 --> 00:20:07,338
What? Have you lost your mind?

269
00:20:07,339 --> 00:20:08,480
Seong Jun!

270
00:20:12,420 --> 00:20:15,518
- Hey. My gosh, are you all right? - What happened?

271
00:20:15,519 --> 00:20:17,548
- Do you know how much this costs? - Are you okay?

272
00:20:17,549 --> 00:20:19,660
Father absolutely treasures this porcelain vase.

273
00:20:21,019 --> 00:20:22,358
It was him.

274
00:20:22,359 --> 00:20:25,660
He broke it. He tried to run away, but I caught him.

275
00:20:26,160 --> 00:20:27,799
- Oh, dear. - Do Jun.

276
00:20:29,099 --> 00:20:30,970
Is that true?

277
00:20:33,839 --> 00:20:35,869
Hold on. Yoon Ki.

278
00:20:36,740 --> 00:20:38,479
This is making me very uncomfortable.

279
00:20:38,480 --> 00:20:42,549
Are you implying that Seong Jun could be lying?

280
00:20:42,950 --> 00:20:44,818
How could you accuse Seong Jun of lying...

281
00:20:44,819 --> 00:20:47,519
He is lying.

282
00:20:47,920 --> 00:20:50,349
What? What do you mean?

283
00:20:50,720 --> 00:20:51,990
The vase...

284
00:20:55,960 --> 00:20:57,329
He's the one who broke it.

285
00:21:00,130 --> 00:21:02,400
He was trying to steal the chairman's belonging.

286
00:21:03,099 --> 00:21:04,529
I caught him in the act.

287
00:21:21,319 --> 00:21:23,150
He got flustered and tried to run away, but...

288
00:21:23,920 --> 00:21:25,089
- Hey! - No!

289
00:21:25,660 --> 00:21:27,519
- Seong Jun! - Do Jun.

290
00:21:27,720 --> 00:21:28,859
- Are you all right? - What is going on?

291
00:21:30,630 --> 00:21:32,759
- Father. - Seong Jun...

292
00:21:34,160 --> 00:21:35,699
It wasn't me, Grandpa.

293
00:21:35,700 --> 00:21:37,970
- I didn't break it. I swear... - Enough.

294
00:21:40,299 --> 00:21:41,640
Shut your mouth.

295
00:21:47,880 --> 00:21:49,380
This happened in 1987,

296
00:21:50,150 --> 00:21:52,379
at the 60th birthday party for your grandfather,

297
00:21:52,380 --> 00:21:53,720
former Chairman Jin.

298
00:21:55,019 --> 00:21:56,650
Year 1987.

299
00:21:57,819 --> 00:21:59,359
Chairman Jin Yang Cheol.

300
00:22:02,690 --> 00:22:03,729
And his 60th birthday party.

301
00:22:03,730 --> 00:22:07,099
You smashed the Goryeo celadon that he cherished...

302
00:22:07,900 --> 00:22:10,829
and was scolded by him for the first time.

303
00:22:11,799 --> 00:22:12,940
The smashed vase?

304
00:22:15,069 --> 00:22:16,170
Seong Jun.

305
00:22:17,470 --> 00:22:19,440
Do you know what you did wrong?

306
00:22:22,450 --> 00:22:23,480
Come here.

307
00:22:26,619 --> 00:22:27,720
Sit down.

308
00:22:34,890 --> 00:22:38,599
You see, I don't care about this vase.

309
00:22:39,960 --> 00:22:43,500
Seong Jun, you will continue my legacy...

310
00:22:44,029 --> 00:22:46,700
and become the owner of Soonyang in the future.

311
00:22:47,900 --> 00:22:48,910
Okay?

312
00:22:51,140 --> 00:22:53,180
Everything you say...

313
00:22:54,140 --> 00:22:55,880
and do...

314
00:22:57,109 --> 00:22:59,119
could make or break ten thousand employees' livelihoods.

315
00:23:00,950 --> 00:23:04,190
Even their families' livelihoods will depend on you.

316
00:23:09,289 --> 00:23:12,799
Yet you can't even keep your emotions under control?

317
00:23:13,329 --> 00:23:14,869
Acting up like this...

318
00:23:18,700 --> 00:23:19,799
It wasn't an adequate quality...

319
00:23:20,769 --> 00:23:21,869
"Isn't an adequate quality..."

320
00:23:22,970 --> 00:23:24,109
isn't an adequate quality...

321
00:23:24,980 --> 00:23:27,779
"in someone who will run a business that is Soonyang."

322
00:23:28,910 --> 00:23:31,619
in someone who will run a business...

323
00:23:32,920 --> 00:23:34,579
that is Soonyang.

324
00:23:37,720 --> 00:23:40,190
What I read in his autobiography is unfolding before my eyes.

325
00:23:40,589 --> 00:23:42,289
It was white porcelain.

326
00:23:44,430 --> 00:23:46,829
My grandfather's vase that I broke.

327
00:23:47,900 --> 00:23:50,430
It wasn't Goryeo celadon. It was a white porcelain vase.

328
00:23:58,279 --> 00:23:59,509
Everything is happening...

329
00:24:00,079 --> 00:24:03,450
exactly as I know it.

330
00:24:17,390 --> 00:24:19,299
The past as I know it.

331
00:24:20,359 --> 00:24:23,029
I'm in Korea in Year 1987.

332
00:24:26,069 --> 00:24:27,170
Then...

333
00:24:29,069 --> 00:24:30,268
If that's the case...

334
00:24:30,269 --> 00:24:32,640
(Jeongsimjae)

335
00:24:46,559 --> 00:24:48,890
(Three Way Restaurant)

336
00:24:55,769 --> 00:24:57,329
That was a great meal. Let's go.

337
00:25:03,839 --> 00:25:05,939
- Thank you. - Did you enjoy the food?

338
00:25:05,940 --> 00:25:08,548
- Yes. - Get back safely.

339
00:25:08,549 --> 00:25:09,710
Hyeon Min?

340
00:25:32,400 --> 00:25:33,470
Mom.

341
00:25:43,950 --> 00:25:45,980
(Ajin Motors)

342
00:25:46,380 --> 00:25:48,518
- Hyeon Min! - You're here.

343
00:25:48,519 --> 00:25:49,690
Dad!

344
00:25:50,049 --> 00:25:51,349
Hi, Hyeon Min!

345
00:25:51,420 --> 00:25:54,659
Lucky you, Hyeon Min! Daddy picked up fried chicken for you.

346
00:25:54,660 --> 00:25:56,130
Who do you like more? Mommy or Daddy?

347
00:25:56,660 --> 00:25:57,829
Mommy!

348
00:25:58,960 --> 00:26:00,429
- I knew it! - I'll do better.

349
00:26:00,430 --> 00:26:02,098
- Do you need a hand? - No, I'm good.

350
00:26:02,099 --> 00:26:03,970
Come on. Let's have this fried chicken.

351
00:26:12,039 --> 00:26:13,910
We found Do Jun.

352
00:26:15,210 --> 00:26:17,009
We'll get there soon too.

353
00:26:18,079 --> 00:26:19,450
Thank you, Mr. Oh.

354
00:26:20,450 --> 00:26:21,480
Okay.

355
00:26:23,690 --> 00:26:25,720
Do Jun is okay. You can put your worries to rest now.

356
00:26:28,160 --> 00:26:29,329
Thank goodness.

357
00:26:32,900 --> 00:26:34,029
Hello...

358
00:26:39,099 --> 00:26:42,369
Are you here alone? Your parents aren't here with you?

359
00:26:46,140 --> 00:26:49,309
Can I have one serving of gukbap?

360
00:26:51,880 --> 00:26:54,849
Sure. You can take that table over there.

361
00:27:54,380 --> 00:27:55,480
Hello...

362
00:27:56,210 --> 00:27:57,309
Do Jun.

363
00:28:03,150 --> 00:28:04,750
What are you doing here?

364
00:28:05,119 --> 00:28:06,420
I was so worried.

365
00:28:09,490 --> 00:28:11,799
Get up. Let's go.

366
00:28:12,930 --> 00:28:14,359
Let's go home.

367
00:28:16,599 --> 00:28:17,670
Let's...

368
00:28:18,869 --> 00:28:20,339
talk at home.

369
00:28:21,569 --> 00:28:22,640
Okay?

370
00:28:47,460 --> 00:28:51,299
(Daeil Bandage)

371
00:28:59,940 --> 00:29:01,009
What's wrong, Do Jun?

372
00:29:02,009 --> 00:29:03,109
What is it?

373
00:29:06,519 --> 00:29:07,819
I'm relieved.

374
00:29:11,190 --> 00:29:12,859
Mom's alive.

375
00:29:15,230 --> 00:29:16,960
I'm so relieved.

376
00:29:24,029 --> 00:29:25,299
Mom's relieved too.

377
00:29:26,970 --> 00:29:28,670
Thank goodness...

378
00:29:31,109 --> 00:29:32,779
I have you.

379
00:29:35,380 --> 00:29:36,549
Don't cry.

380
00:29:49,859 --> 00:29:52,960
That poor thing must've been so scared. Look how he ran away.

381
00:29:55,829 --> 00:29:57,170
Well done.

382
00:29:58,539 --> 00:30:01,869
Way to go.

383
00:30:04,170 --> 00:30:08,308
Your son and grandsons came to see you after ten years.

384
00:30:08,309 --> 00:30:10,549
How could you read a book after kicking them out like that?

385
00:30:11,380 --> 00:30:13,480
My son and grandsons? Who?

386
00:30:14,519 --> 00:30:17,150
I only scolded my eldest grandson,

387
00:30:17,450 --> 00:30:18,859
Seong Jun. No one else.

388
00:30:19,359 --> 00:30:22,358
You can't expect all your children to be the same.

389
00:30:22,359 --> 00:30:25,598
Let at least one of them do what they want.

390
00:30:25,599 --> 00:30:27,629
I fed them and paid for their education,

391
00:30:27,630 --> 00:30:28,730
so I must get my money's worth.

392
00:30:29,400 --> 00:30:31,569
I never invest in things where I can't get my money's worth.

393
00:30:33,900 --> 00:30:36,509
You'd better not coddle Yoon Ki.

394
00:30:40,710 --> 00:30:41,910
The others will turn out like him.

395
00:31:01,859 --> 00:31:05,640
The only person in this family who I know nothing about...

396
00:31:06,099 --> 00:31:09,210
is me, 4-2 Jin Do Jun.

397
00:31:10,809 --> 00:31:14,338
Am I living as Jin Do Jun now because I'm possessed?

398
00:31:14,339 --> 00:31:16,480
(Three Way Restaurant)

399
00:31:22,920 --> 00:31:23,920
(Three Way Restaurant)

400
00:31:24,220 --> 00:31:27,588
- Mom. - Hi, son!

401
00:31:27,589 --> 00:31:28,858
Hey, you. Come here.

402
00:31:28,859 --> 00:31:31,528
- Oh, look at you. - Gosh, stop!

403
00:31:31,529 --> 00:31:34,429
- Run! Go! - Hey, where are you going?

404
00:31:34,430 --> 00:31:38,170
- Oh, nice one. - Let's cheer for your brother!

405
00:31:38,569 --> 00:31:42,009
- Nice. - Well done.

406
00:31:43,069 --> 00:31:44,410
Or did I simply travel back in time?

407
00:31:45,410 --> 00:31:47,579
If not that... Have I been reincarnated?

408
00:31:48,480 --> 00:31:49,750
How did this happen?

409
00:31:50,809 --> 00:31:52,349
(Daily Schedule, Timetable)

410
00:31:57,849 --> 00:31:59,160
Why are you still up?

411
00:32:00,059 --> 00:32:01,089
It's getting late.

412
00:32:04,630 --> 00:32:08,000
Do Jun, what happened today... It must've been a lot for you.

413
00:32:21,309 --> 00:32:22,410
At first,

414
00:32:23,450 --> 00:32:25,250
I felt the same way.

415
00:32:26,750 --> 00:32:28,750
"What am I doing here?"

416
00:32:29,250 --> 00:32:31,690
"I don't belong in this world."

417
00:32:32,990 --> 00:32:36,589
I couldn't understand them. It was very frustrating.

418
00:32:37,690 --> 00:32:39,799
You felt the same way?

419
00:32:42,130 --> 00:32:43,199
Does that mean...

420
00:32:43,200 --> 00:32:46,339
It felt so foreign to me. I was scared,

421
00:32:46,940 --> 00:32:47,940
and it was uncomfortable.

422
00:32:48,910 --> 00:32:52,640
I almost regretted marrying your dad.

423
00:32:55,509 --> 00:32:58,180
But now, it's not so bad.

424
00:33:00,980 --> 00:33:06,359
I've found a reason to accept them as my family.

425
00:33:07,720 --> 00:33:09,289
A reason to accept them as your family?

426
00:33:09,789 --> 00:33:12,730
You and Hyeong Jun.

427
00:33:14,160 --> 00:33:15,400
Do Jun.

428
00:33:16,529 --> 00:33:20,099
I'm certain that you'll find your reason too, one day.

429
00:33:39,859 --> 00:33:42,589
All the companies are dropping their prices for their 64K DRAMs.

430
00:33:44,190 --> 00:33:46,430
Soonyang Semiconductor started exporting them this month.

431
00:33:47,630 --> 00:33:49,729
Japan and the US are already dominating the market.

432
00:33:49,730 --> 00:33:52,029
So if they're charging less than half of what we're asking for,

433
00:33:52,500 --> 00:33:55,240
Soonyang Semiconductor will not survive in the market, sir.

434
00:33:58,710 --> 00:33:59,779
What time is it now...

435
00:34:01,079 --> 00:34:02,180
in New York?

436
00:34:04,079 --> 00:34:05,180
It's 9pm, sir.

437
00:34:05,420 --> 00:34:07,518
Is Im Pil Sung in New York now?

438
00:34:07,519 --> 00:34:09,388
I'll tell him to give you a call at once.

439
00:34:09,389 --> 00:34:10,889
No, don't wake him up.

440
00:34:12,519 --> 00:34:14,519
Just tell him to fax it over when he wakes up.

441
00:34:15,190 --> 00:34:17,329
- Fax? What do you need, sir? - His resignation letter.

442
00:34:17,789 --> 00:34:18,860
Pardon me?

443
00:34:25,230 --> 00:34:28,339
I didn't know that I had a knife held to my throat...

444
00:34:28,340 --> 00:34:30,340
until I read that newspaper.

445
00:34:33,639 --> 00:34:35,039
Do you think it's acceptable?

446
00:34:37,949 --> 00:34:39,920
Did he go to the US to eat hamburgers?

447
00:34:41,380 --> 00:34:43,119
I'm done paying for his hamburgers.

448
00:34:45,960 --> 00:34:47,158
I saw the news, Father.

449
00:34:47,159 --> 00:34:50,989
The American companies slashed their price from 3 to 1.80 dollars.

450
00:34:51,389 --> 00:34:53,800
And the Japanese companies said they'd sell it for 0.30 dollars.

451
00:34:54,860 --> 00:34:57,199
If we sell ours at the price the Japanese companies are offering,

452
00:34:57,469 --> 00:35:00,599
we'll lose 130 million dollars this year alone.

453
00:35:01,440 --> 00:35:02,709
We're like the shrimp...

454
00:35:02,710 --> 00:35:04,840
getting squashed between two whales that are fighting.

455
00:35:04,940 --> 00:35:05,980
The semiconductor business...

456
00:35:07,409 --> 00:35:08,539
Let's just give up here.

457
00:35:09,349 --> 00:35:10,880
I'm afraid we've come too far.

458
00:35:11,050 --> 00:35:12,109
The initial investment alone...

459
00:35:12,110 --> 00:35:14,050
Right, so let's cut our losses and call it quits.

460
00:35:15,449 --> 00:35:17,420
Let's stop trying to fill the bottomless pit.

461
00:35:18,349 --> 00:35:20,320
Youngjin Semiconductor has given up too.

462
00:35:21,019 --> 00:35:22,960
They're being sold to a Japanese company.

463
00:35:24,829 --> 00:35:27,699
Think of the question you always ask us.

464
00:35:28,699 --> 00:35:30,400
Will the semiconductor business bring in money?

465
00:35:33,639 --> 00:35:36,309
(Jeongsimjae)

466
00:35:41,280 --> 00:35:43,679
What brings you by at this hour?

467
00:35:44,079 --> 00:35:47,150
I'm sorry for causing you concern yesterday.

468
00:35:52,460 --> 00:35:54,489
I'm here to apologize to Grandpa.

469
00:35:55,630 --> 00:35:59,960
Look at you talking like a grown man. You're so mature.

470
00:36:00,530 --> 00:36:03,099
Come with me. He's upstairs in his study.

471
00:36:03,630 --> 00:36:04,670
Come on.

472
00:36:11,269 --> 00:36:13,309
Kids should behave like kids.

473
00:36:13,940 --> 00:36:17,349
Is she naive? Or is she becoming dense?

474
00:36:18,010 --> 00:36:20,250
- Hey. - I'm talking about Mother.

475
00:36:20,449 --> 00:36:21,449
Oh.

476
00:36:22,289 --> 00:36:23,619
Isn't it so obvious?

477
00:36:23,820 --> 00:36:26,559
Clearly, he memorized what his father told him to say.

478
00:36:26,820 --> 00:36:28,219
He's talking like a man in his 40s.

479
00:36:31,389 --> 00:36:32,829
Wait here.

480
00:36:33,159 --> 00:36:35,500
He'll be out soon.

481
00:36:36,199 --> 00:36:37,699
You can watch TV if you get bored.

482
00:36:38,030 --> 00:36:39,070
- Okay. - All right, then.

483
00:36:44,739 --> 00:36:45,940
("Two Kims Continue to Disagree on Single Candidacy")

484
00:36:46,309 --> 00:36:47,909
("Last Minute Conflict Surrounding Single Candidacy")

485
00:36:56,320 --> 00:36:58,090
You should deliver the campaign fund yourself...

486
00:36:58,389 --> 00:37:00,820
and meet him in person.

487
00:37:01,119 --> 00:37:02,119
What?

488
00:37:03,230 --> 00:37:05,230
The general election will take place in April next year.

489
00:37:06,199 --> 00:37:07,360
You need a nomination.

490
00:37:09,199 --> 00:37:12,538
Oh, right. Honey, you know everything.

491
00:37:12,539 --> 00:37:14,269
You sure take after Father.

492
00:37:20,110 --> 00:37:21,809
I heard you had visitors from Cheongwadae yesterday.

493
00:37:22,610 --> 00:37:24,849
Did they ask you to back Roh Tae Woo's campaign?

494
00:37:28,579 --> 00:37:32,360
Mr. Lee only listens and never spills what he hears.

495
00:37:33,119 --> 00:37:35,829
I'm your daughter, Father. Of course, I know that much.

496
00:37:36,030 --> 00:37:37,360
You silly goose.

497
00:37:37,960 --> 00:37:39,099
Take a seat.

498
00:37:40,099 --> 00:37:41,230
You too.

499
00:37:43,329 --> 00:37:45,230
Instead of calling you to Cheongwadae,

500
00:37:45,469 --> 00:37:49,070
they came all the way here. It means the tables have turned.

501
00:37:49,940 --> 00:37:52,038
It tells me that Roh Tae Woo is at a disadvantage.

502
00:37:52,039 --> 00:37:54,609
I'm not surprised. After all the protests and uprisings...

503
00:37:54,610 --> 00:37:56,948
to end the military dictatorship,

504
00:37:56,949 --> 00:37:59,179
who'd want to vote for another Military Academy graduate?

505
00:37:59,619 --> 00:38:02,150
Unless the entire nation is suffering from amnesia collectively.

506
00:38:02,420 --> 00:38:04,289
The two Kims will agree on single candidacy soon.

507
00:38:04,519 --> 00:38:06,718
The opposition power will win this time, Father.

508
00:38:06,719 --> 00:38:08,159
That being said,

509
00:38:08,590 --> 00:38:11,389
shouldn't you decide which candidate to support now?

510
00:38:11,789 --> 00:38:13,959
Between DJ and YS, choose the one who's more likely to win...

511
00:38:13,960 --> 00:38:17,400
Right. So who would that be?

512
00:38:17,630 --> 00:38:19,199
DJ, obviously.

513
00:38:19,469 --> 00:38:21,368
He is supported by all the student and civic groups...

514
00:38:21,369 --> 00:38:23,909
that helped establish the direct election system.

515
00:38:25,739 --> 00:38:28,039
Dong Ki, you should never get into politics.

516
00:38:28,309 --> 00:38:30,610
We should support YS, not DJ.

517
00:38:31,050 --> 00:38:33,049
I know DJ has many fans, but he also has many enemies.

518
00:38:33,050 --> 00:38:36,050
When it's a neck-and-neck fight, the one with less enemies will win.

519
00:38:37,449 --> 00:38:39,590
Aren't you saying that because you dislike DJ?

520
00:38:40,590 --> 00:38:42,529
I heard Kim Dae Jung was against...

521
00:38:42,530 --> 00:38:45,429
nominating Chang Je since he worked as a public security prosecutor.

522
00:38:46,599 --> 00:38:48,300
Why are you roping Chang Je into this?

523
00:38:48,630 --> 00:38:51,000
I am saying these things for the sake of the company's future.

524
00:38:52,469 --> 00:38:54,670
- Father! - Be quiet.

525
00:38:55,769 --> 00:38:58,239
I'm sorry for causing you concern, Father.

526
00:38:58,940 --> 00:39:00,738
- Mr. Lee. - Yes, sir.

527
00:39:00,739 --> 00:39:02,449
As for their approval ratings,

528
00:39:02,980 --> 00:39:05,150
get Soonyang Economic Research Institute to look into it.

529
00:39:06,179 --> 00:39:09,119
Tell them to find out which one of them deserves my money more.

530
00:39:09,349 --> 00:39:10,389
Yes, sir.

531
00:39:12,519 --> 00:39:13,920
Now, get out.

532
00:39:17,429 --> 00:39:19,960
- Oh. - Hey, aren't you Yoon Ki's son?

533
00:39:20,599 --> 00:39:23,929
I'm here to apologize to Grandpa for what happened yesterday.

534
00:39:25,329 --> 00:39:29,269
Oh, my. Yoon Ki always had a sly side to him.

535
00:39:29,840 --> 00:39:31,468
After not visiting us once for ten years,

536
00:39:31,469 --> 00:39:34,280
he now sends his son here every day.

537
00:39:34,809 --> 00:39:37,150
He came all the way here by himself because his parents told him to?

538
00:39:37,949 --> 00:39:39,320
He sure takes after his father.

539
00:39:39,949 --> 00:39:42,179
Good-looking and calculating.

540
00:39:44,420 --> 00:39:47,090
Your youngest son's child is here to see you, sir.

541
00:39:47,559 --> 00:39:49,860
I only have two sons. I didn't know I had another son!

542
00:39:51,059 --> 00:39:53,000
I will talk to him and send him home, sir.

543
00:39:56,500 --> 00:39:58,070
Come with us. Let's go downstairs.

544
00:40:00,139 --> 00:40:01,969
Please tell Grandpa...

545
00:40:03,070 --> 00:40:06,739
that I'm here to pay for the vase that broke yesterday.

546
00:40:07,809 --> 00:40:09,250
That punk.

547
00:40:09,280 --> 00:40:11,879
Hey! You little brat.

548
00:40:11,880 --> 00:40:15,889
Hey, do you even know how much that vase costs?

549
00:40:16,349 --> 00:40:17,519
Five bills?

550
00:40:18,119 --> 00:40:20,859
It can't cost more than that.

551
00:40:20,860 --> 00:40:23,260
Five bills? What? Five dollars?

552
00:40:23,929 --> 00:40:25,230
Or 50 dollars?

553
00:40:28,030 --> 00:40:29,099
No, five million dollars.

554
00:40:31,130 --> 00:40:32,969
What? Five million?

555
00:40:37,139 --> 00:40:40,239
Wouldn't that be enough to fund a presidential election campaign?

556
00:40:43,250 --> 00:40:44,610
What? Presidential election campaign?

557
00:40:47,119 --> 00:40:48,949
Please let Grandpa know.

558
00:40:49,619 --> 00:40:53,159
If it were me, I'd back Roh Tae Woo's campaign.

559
00:40:56,659 --> 00:40:59,530
Roh Tae Woo will become President.

560
00:41:02,630 --> 00:41:05,530
Did you eavesdrop on the adults' conversation?

561
00:41:06,639 --> 00:41:08,969
Clearly, your parents couldn't teach you any better.

562
00:41:09,469 --> 00:41:11,610
Is this how your parents taught you?

563
00:41:12,880 --> 00:41:15,909
No one teaches their children to be so brazen.

564
00:41:16,650 --> 00:41:18,949
Just like how no one tells their children...

565
00:41:19,110 --> 00:41:20,649
to steal their grandfather's things.

566
00:41:20,650 --> 00:41:22,320
- Do Jun. - What?

567
00:41:24,420 --> 00:41:26,519
Young Ki, you must be getting old.

568
00:41:26,820 --> 00:41:29,590
He's just a kid. Why are you getting so worked up?

569
00:41:29,960 --> 00:41:32,489
He's read some newspapers, so he's trying to sound like an adult.

570
00:41:33,059 --> 00:41:35,158
Once DJ and YS agree on single candidacy,

571
00:41:35,159 --> 00:41:37,069
Roh Tae Woo can't win.

572
00:41:37,070 --> 00:41:38,500
I assure you that he won't win.

573
00:41:38,969 --> 00:41:40,000
Single candidacy?

574
00:41:41,400 --> 00:41:44,340
Do you think the two of them will actually reach an agreement?

575
00:41:52,309 --> 00:41:53,550
I do not think so.

576
00:41:56,989 --> 00:41:59,050
Now, that should be enough to compensate him for the broken vase.

577
00:41:59,889 --> 00:42:02,019
I'll be off, then.

578
00:42:03,389 --> 00:42:04,460
Goodness.

579
00:42:07,030 --> 00:42:11,429
Oh, my. Yoon Ki did a great job, bringing up such a smart boy.

580
00:42:12,500 --> 00:42:13,639
Oh, sorry.

581
00:42:14,139 --> 00:42:15,239
Of course, it's nonsense.

582
00:42:15,500 --> 00:42:17,738
So many people are rooting for single candidacy.

583
00:42:17,739 --> 00:42:20,110
They won't betray the majority opinion.

584
00:42:20,409 --> 00:42:22,279
Both YS and DJ...

585
00:42:22,280 --> 00:42:25,079
have come this far because of their devotion...

586
00:42:25,380 --> 00:42:26,920
to the democratization of the nation.

587
00:42:27,880 --> 00:42:30,389
They won't gamble on their political careers.

588
00:42:31,690 --> 00:42:32,719
Exactly.

589
00:42:35,360 --> 00:42:38,360
Mr. Oh, take Mr. Chairman's grandson home.

590
00:42:41,000 --> 00:42:43,900
Sir, there's breaking news about the presidential election.

591
00:42:44,869 --> 00:42:46,539
You should see it.

592
00:42:47,239 --> 00:42:48,340
What's the matter?

593
00:42:50,369 --> 00:42:52,678
Kim Young Sam and Kim Dae Jung of the Democratic Party...

594
00:42:52,679 --> 00:42:56,409
decided against single candidacy earlier today.

595
00:42:56,550 --> 00:42:59,848
Kim Dae Jung clearly expressed...

596
00:42:59,849 --> 00:43:01,820
that he was against the party convention,

597
00:43:02,079 --> 00:43:05,348
which means they will both run for President.

598
00:43:05,349 --> 00:43:06,518
Father.

599
00:43:06,519 --> 00:43:08,988
Kim Young Sam and Kim Dae Jung met again...

600
00:43:08,989 --> 00:43:11,428
- Father! - to negotiate the details...

601
00:43:11,429 --> 00:43:13,230
regarding single candidacy but failed to reach an agreement.

602
00:43:13,530 --> 00:43:16,529
Their talk ended when they decided...

603
00:43:16,530 --> 00:43:19,468
to postpone the deadline to next Monday,

604
00:43:19,469 --> 00:43:21,269
which is when Kim Dae Jung would have to reply by.

605
00:43:23,039 --> 00:43:24,710
Wait, stop!

606
00:43:31,110 --> 00:43:32,980
Mr. Chairman would like to speak with you.

607
00:43:33,780 --> 00:43:34,849
Right now.

608
00:43:38,849 --> 00:43:39,920
Tell me.

609
00:43:41,619 --> 00:43:43,460
How did you know they'd decide against single candidacy?

610
00:43:44,530 --> 00:43:47,159
I wouldn't be able to concede. That's why.

611
00:43:47,559 --> 00:43:48,699
Because I'd get greedy.

612
00:43:49,699 --> 00:43:52,429
When three candidates are running for class president,

613
00:43:52,900 --> 00:43:55,000
the top two candidates will never join hands...

614
00:43:55,800 --> 00:43:58,139
because they both believe that they will win.

615
00:43:59,170 --> 00:44:02,639
Rather, they'll do whatever it takes to make each other lose.

616
00:44:03,079 --> 00:44:05,480
They'll bad-mouth each other and fight.

617
00:44:06,280 --> 00:44:09,119
Then their teachers and classmates...

618
00:44:09,619 --> 00:44:12,050
will realize that they, in fact, don't deserve the position.

619
00:44:12,719 --> 00:44:15,389
Just like that, they'll drag each other down.

620
00:44:15,489 --> 00:44:18,630
So the one who was least likely to win will end up winning.

621
00:44:19,429 --> 00:44:20,829
You mean he'll win by default.

622
00:44:21,599 --> 00:44:24,670
Roh Tae Woo will become President, by default.

623
00:44:25,070 --> 00:44:28,739
So I should back Roh Tae Woo. Is that right?

624
00:44:31,010 --> 00:44:34,409
If I were you, I'd give him the money before he became number one.

625
00:44:35,179 --> 00:44:38,550
A lot more than the amount he may be expecting.

626
00:44:39,849 --> 00:44:42,750
He'll be grateful if you give it to him when he's still number three.

627
00:44:43,289 --> 00:44:44,989
But if you wait until he becomes number one,

628
00:44:45,489 --> 00:44:47,489
he'll take it for granted.

629
00:44:55,699 --> 00:44:58,400
- Mr. Lee. - Yes, sir.

630
00:44:58,900 --> 00:45:01,440
Tell Mr. Oh to have the car ready.

631
00:45:02,070 --> 00:45:03,170
Yes, sir.

632
00:45:07,010 --> 00:45:09,949
- Hey. - Mr. Oh, have the car ready.

633
00:45:10,449 --> 00:45:12,280
Let me ask you one more question, then.

634
00:45:12,650 --> 00:45:15,920
I believe I've already paid you for the broken vase, Grandpa.

635
00:45:16,690 --> 00:45:18,889
It's nothing difficult. It's just a quiz.

636
00:45:19,050 --> 00:45:21,789
Then there must be a prize for getting it right.

637
00:45:22,159 --> 00:45:23,230
Because it's a quiz.

638
00:45:29,059 --> 00:45:30,969
I don't like to do things for free either.

639
00:45:33,570 --> 00:45:37,038
We talked about how number 3 can win by default because number 1 and 2...

640
00:45:37,039 --> 00:45:38,869
are busy fighting, right?

641
00:45:39,880 --> 00:45:41,439
But there's this saying too.

642
00:45:41,440 --> 00:45:44,150
"The shrimp is squashed to death when two whales fight."

643
00:45:45,679 --> 00:45:48,320
Then do you think there's a way...

644
00:45:49,489 --> 00:45:52,860
for the shrimp to beat the whales?

645
00:46:07,670 --> 00:46:09,670
You're just like other kids, after all.

646
00:46:23,550 --> 00:46:24,550
Hey.

647
00:46:25,550 --> 00:46:26,559
Come here.

648
00:46:33,199 --> 00:46:34,260
How did you know...

649
00:46:35,400 --> 00:46:36,929
the candidates won't be unified?

650
00:46:38,329 --> 00:46:39,429
Yoon Ki, no.

651
00:46:40,769 --> 00:46:42,500
Did your father tell you so?

652
00:46:46,980 --> 00:46:48,110
My brother said so.

653
00:46:48,980 --> 00:46:50,010
Your brother?

654
00:46:51,010 --> 00:46:52,610
This is what we do in times like these.

655
00:46:53,849 --> 00:46:56,650
"It's obvious at a single glance."

656
00:46:57,650 --> 00:46:58,719
What's with this punk?

657
00:46:58,849 --> 00:47:00,460
That's a buzzword by Hwang Ki Soon.

658
00:47:01,059 --> 00:47:02,090
Hwang Ki...

659
00:47:02,320 --> 00:47:04,360
You punk! That's not the way you should talk to your elders.

660
00:47:06,829 --> 00:47:10,130
Do you think there's a way for a shrimp to win against a whale?

661
00:47:11,099 --> 00:47:13,469
I guess you can't give up on the semiconductor, Chairman Jin.

662
00:47:16,070 --> 00:47:18,010
Why do you think I'm so set on semiconductor?

663
00:47:21,340 --> 00:47:25,679
Last summer, in Mokpo, Ulsan, and Changwon,

664
00:47:26,650 --> 00:47:29,449
when the laborers of our factories put on headbands...

665
00:47:30,219 --> 00:47:32,449
and stood there protesting...

666
00:47:32,989 --> 00:47:36,190
with cranes and excavators, asking me for a raise...

667
00:47:36,530 --> 00:47:37,730
and the formation of a labor union,

668
00:47:39,860 --> 00:47:42,969
I only thought about this...

669
00:47:45,230 --> 00:47:47,369
in my head.

670
00:47:50,510 --> 00:47:53,480
I am done doing business by using laborers.

671
00:47:54,510 --> 00:47:55,579
Then...

672
00:47:55,909 --> 00:47:56,909
From now on,

673
00:47:58,349 --> 00:48:00,480
we must do business with technologies to make a living.

674
00:48:03,920 --> 00:48:04,920
Semiconductor is...

675
00:48:05,849 --> 00:48:08,519
the future business of Soonyang.

676
00:48:10,690 --> 00:48:11,729
I see.

677
00:48:11,730 --> 00:48:13,329
Do you ask if it'll be worth any money?

678
00:48:17,869 --> 00:48:20,239
Am I the only one who sees this?

679
00:48:23,309 --> 00:48:25,969
Why is there nobody else who can think like this old man?

680
00:48:28,610 --> 00:48:30,578
We have to make an astronomical investment,

681
00:48:30,579 --> 00:48:32,179
but we do not know if it'll be a success.

682
00:48:33,179 --> 00:48:36,119
The semiconductor business is nothing but a risk,

683
00:48:36,690 --> 00:48:38,219
no, more like gambling at this point, Chairman Jin.

684
00:48:43,360 --> 00:48:44,629
Once our finances look better...

685
00:48:44,630 --> 00:48:47,360
by overseas construction business with the government's cooperation,

686
00:48:47,699 --> 00:48:50,329
why don't you resume the semiconductor business then?

687
00:48:51,170 --> 00:48:52,800
Do you know what democratization is?

688
00:48:54,400 --> 00:48:55,440
I'm not sure.

689
00:48:56,269 --> 00:49:00,380
Before, only a single soldier was after the money in my pocket.

690
00:49:01,539 --> 00:49:04,949
That turned into three civilians.

691
00:49:06,449 --> 00:49:07,650
That's democratization.

692
00:49:27,039 --> 00:49:28,440
(Best Taste! Best Quality!)

693
00:49:39,750 --> 00:49:41,280
Please give this to the president.

694
00:49:42,420 --> 00:49:44,550
That I believe he will surely put an end...

695
00:49:45,320 --> 00:49:47,219
to this era of military dictatorship.

696
00:49:48,719 --> 00:49:49,730
Thank you.

697
00:49:53,730 --> 00:49:55,360
(People's Hiking Club, 1987)

698
00:49:56,929 --> 00:50:00,699
Our chairman was touched deeply by your character...

699
00:50:01,369 --> 00:50:04,710
when you said you will not take any political retaliation.

700
00:50:10,679 --> 00:50:12,179
Please use this...

701
00:50:12,750 --> 00:50:15,579
for the sake of peace in Korea just as you wanted.

702
00:50:16,219 --> 00:50:18,089
The campaign of Roh Tae Woo of Democratic Justice Party was...

703
00:50:18,090 --> 00:50:19,960
held in the square in front of Gwangju Station.

704
00:50:20,389 --> 00:50:23,018
As soon as the campaign began at 2pm,

705
00:50:23,019 --> 00:50:26,730
young people and university students came out protesting...

706
00:50:26,829 --> 00:50:29,459
and chanting Kim Dae Jung's name.

707
00:50:29,460 --> 00:50:30,469
("Tear Gas Dropped During Roh Tae Woo's Speech")

708
00:50:40,909 --> 00:50:42,009
(October 1987, "Business Weekly")

709
00:50:42,010 --> 00:50:43,079
(Korea's Semiconductor in Crisis, Youngjin Semiconductor to Be Sold)

710
00:50:43,679 --> 00:50:46,848
We talked about how number 3 can win by default because number 1 and 2...

711
00:50:46,849 --> 00:50:48,320
are busy fighting, right?

712
00:50:48,579 --> 00:50:52,250
Then do you think there's a way...

713
00:50:52,719 --> 00:50:54,989
for the shrimp to beat the whales?

714
00:50:55,119 --> 00:50:57,659
("Small Korean Businesses Sacrificed in This Global Chicken Game")

715
00:50:58,559 --> 00:50:59,559
Small?

716
00:50:59,560 --> 00:51:01,229
Snack time.

717
00:51:01,230 --> 00:51:02,300
I finally realized...

718
00:51:02,659 --> 00:51:05,400
the answer to Chairman Jin Yang Cheol's quiz.

719
00:51:08,539 --> 00:51:11,639
Grandma, I have something I'd like to say to Grandpa.

720
00:51:12,170 --> 00:51:13,409
Is he home right now?

721
00:51:16,309 --> 00:51:18,010
He's on a business trip to Baghdad?

722
00:51:41,000 --> 00:51:43,099
Then when will he return?

723
00:51:47,239 --> 00:51:49,239
October 29th.

724
00:51:54,780 --> 00:51:55,949
By any chance,

725
00:51:56,920 --> 00:51:59,320
do you know what his flight number is?

726
00:52:09,059 --> 00:52:11,000
Okay. Thank you, Grandma.

727
00:52:11,300 --> 00:52:13,030
I'll call you again next time.

728
00:52:13,969 --> 00:52:15,039
Bye.

729
00:52:20,840 --> 00:52:22,110
CAL 828.

730
00:52:23,610 --> 00:52:25,308
The CAL incident of 1987.

731
00:52:25,309 --> 00:52:28,249
An aircraft with 95 passengers and 20 flight attendants...

732
00:52:28,250 --> 00:52:30,789
went missing above Yangon, Myanmar.

733
00:52:31,820 --> 00:52:34,789
Chairman Jin Yang Cheol will return to Seoul...

734
00:52:35,460 --> 00:52:37,230
on that very plane, CAL 828.

735
00:52:37,929 --> 00:52:42,329
At midnight in Korea, it will take off from Baghdad Airport,

736
00:52:44,070 --> 00:52:45,130
in three hours.

737
00:52:46,369 --> 00:52:48,869
I only have three hours of time...

738
00:52:50,710 --> 00:52:52,039
to save Chairman Jin Yang Cheol.

739
00:52:54,039 --> 00:52:56,980
So they refuse to accept the terms we suggested?

740
00:52:57,380 --> 00:53:00,579
If we press them by using the royal family, it can happen.

741
00:53:02,050 --> 00:53:03,150
The royal family again?

742
00:53:03,820 --> 00:53:05,749
The second son of the King, Prince Hussein,

743
00:53:05,750 --> 00:53:07,690
plans on visiting Abu Dhabi...

744
00:53:07,860 --> 00:53:09,489
on the same flight as us, CAL 828.

745
00:53:11,590 --> 00:53:15,300
Mr. Lee right here is telling me to do a sales pitch...

746
00:53:15,460 --> 00:53:18,300
even when I'm on my flight.

747
00:53:24,039 --> 00:53:25,070
(Korea Telecom)

748
00:53:33,949 --> 00:53:35,249
You have reached the customer service center.

749
00:53:35,250 --> 00:53:37,489
It's a bombing attack. We must stop this terrorist attack.

750
00:53:38,119 --> 00:53:39,189
A bombing attack?

751
00:53:39,190 --> 00:53:43,118
On flight CAL 828 from Baghdad Airport to Seoul,

752
00:53:43,119 --> 00:53:45,230
a North Korean agent will plant a bomb.

753
00:53:45,829 --> 00:53:48,099
If you aren't prepared, it will blow up in open waters...

754
00:53:48,760 --> 00:53:50,399
and kill two passengers.

755
00:53:50,400 --> 00:53:51,499
Hey, kid.

756
00:53:51,500 --> 00:53:54,339
A prank call on bombing attacks and abductions of an aircraft is...

757
00:53:54,340 --> 00:53:56,609
a crime you will be punished for and will have to pay for damages...

758
00:53:56,610 --> 00:53:59,209
- through a civil action. - It's not a prank. It's true.

759
00:53:59,210 --> 00:54:01,539
Hundreds of lives are in danger.

760
00:54:02,010 --> 00:54:04,010
You have to save them!

761
00:54:06,949 --> 00:54:09,079
Hello?

762
00:54:21,530 --> 00:54:22,559
Of course.

763
00:54:23,599 --> 00:54:25,329
No one will be able to believe me.

764
00:54:26,969 --> 00:54:28,739
And that I am from the future.

765
00:54:29,599 --> 00:54:31,539
That I already know everything that will happen...

766
00:54:33,239 --> 00:54:34,639
from now on.

767
00:54:37,210 --> 00:54:40,249
(Korea Telecom)

768
00:54:40,250 --> 00:54:43,920
It's even hard for me to believe everything that's happening now.

769
00:54:50,230 --> 00:54:52,630
Grandma, open the door, please.

770
00:54:53,360 --> 00:54:55,030
We have no time, Grandma!

771
00:54:55,659 --> 00:54:56,699
Grandma!

772
00:55:04,510 --> 00:55:06,440
- Bring him a blanket, please. - Yes.

773
00:55:07,210 --> 00:55:09,880
Goodness, what brings you here at this hour?

774
00:55:10,280 --> 00:55:13,150
Grandma, can you let me speak to Grandpa?

775
00:55:13,550 --> 00:55:15,320
There is something I must tell him.

776
00:55:15,849 --> 00:55:17,389
We have no time, Grandma.

777
00:55:18,949 --> 00:55:21,788
Chairman Jin is in a meeting with local Iraqi staff.

778
00:55:21,789 --> 00:55:24,230
I will pass on a message if you leave it with me.

779
00:55:24,429 --> 00:55:25,659
Yes, I am ready.

780
00:55:26,760 --> 00:55:30,800
I finally found out the answer to the quiz you asked, Grandpa.

781
00:55:31,769 --> 00:55:34,300
A way for a shrimp to beat the whales.

782
00:55:35,400 --> 00:55:39,039
Once you see this note, I believe that you will...

783
00:55:39,969 --> 00:55:41,110
change your flight.

784
00:55:48,780 --> 00:55:51,050
- Great work. - Great work.

785
00:55:54,420 --> 00:55:56,219
Did anyone call from Seoul?

786
00:55:57,429 --> 00:55:59,460
- No, nobody called. - Good.

787
00:56:00,559 --> 00:56:01,760
Where is it?

788
00:56:03,469 --> 00:56:04,769
Man, where did it go?

789
00:56:10,510 --> 00:56:11,940
- Mr. Kim. - Yes!

790
00:56:12,239 --> 00:56:13,809
- Did you lose something? - No!

791
00:56:15,780 --> 00:56:17,908
Check if anything is missing before we go to the airport.

792
00:56:17,909 --> 00:56:19,150
Yes, sir.

793
00:56:20,380 --> 00:56:21,579
Great work, sir.

794
00:56:25,389 --> 00:56:26,489
Where is this thing?

795
00:56:33,059 --> 00:56:34,130
Thank you.

796
00:56:49,909 --> 00:56:53,078
Next story. On October 6th, HHI-1200, embarked the equipment...

797
00:56:53,079 --> 00:56:57,019
to build the Korean Research Center and left for Antarctica from Ulsan.

798
00:56:58,389 --> 00:57:01,659
Yesterday night, I began to hate you

799
00:57:02,619 --> 00:57:05,629
After 94 days, the ship stopped momentarily...

800
00:57:05,630 --> 00:57:07,460
at Port Valparaiso, their last stopover.

801
00:57:08,130 --> 00:57:11,469
- I began to hate you - Do Jun was watching it first.

802
00:57:14,099 --> 00:57:16,468
- Darn it. - They will have arrived...

803
00:57:16,469 --> 00:57:18,408
- by next month at the latest... - I'm watching the news right now!

804
00:57:18,409 --> 00:57:20,379
on King George Island.

805
00:57:20,380 --> 00:57:21,380
Jin Do Jun.

806
00:57:21,381 --> 00:57:24,049
An aircraft with 95 passengers and 20 flight attendants...

807
00:57:24,050 --> 00:57:26,678
went missing above Yangon, Myanmar.

808
00:57:26,679 --> 00:57:30,619
The details of the accident is yet to be discovered.

809
00:57:30,849 --> 00:57:32,848
Let us report to you...

810
00:57:32,849 --> 00:57:36,218
the details we know so far along with the list of passengers.

811
00:57:36,219 --> 00:57:39,059
Let us connect to the reporter.

812
00:57:46,840 --> 00:57:48,539
Have you checked the list of passengers?

813
00:57:48,840 --> 00:57:50,070
Young Ki is on it.

814
00:57:52,610 --> 00:57:55,679
Yes, is that the final list of passengers...

815
00:57:56,710 --> 00:58:00,010
from Baghdad Airport?

816
00:58:10,119 --> 00:58:11,230
No, right?

817
00:58:13,530 --> 00:58:16,829
Your father wouldn't pass away in such vain.

818
00:58:20,840 --> 00:58:22,999
I'm... I'm sorry, Mother.

819
00:58:23,000 --> 00:58:26,109
Oh no, Mother! Mother!

820
00:58:26,110 --> 00:58:28,710
- Mother. - Mother! Oh no.

821
00:58:28,840 --> 00:58:31,109
Water, bring her some water!

822
00:58:31,110 --> 00:58:33,820
Goodness, Mother. You poor woman.

823
00:58:37,989 --> 00:58:41,219
Chairman Jin's autobiography did not mention the CAL incident.

824
00:58:42,420 --> 00:58:43,829
Then did something change...

825
00:58:45,030 --> 00:58:47,099
because I came here?

826
00:58:51,000 --> 00:58:52,400
Was I too late?

827
00:58:52,769 --> 00:58:54,670
If I had remembered a little earlier,

828
00:58:56,699 --> 00:58:58,769
could I have saved Chairman Jin?

829
00:59:01,780 --> 00:59:03,239
Get it together!

830
00:59:08,320 --> 00:59:11,090
- No! - No, Father!

831
00:59:14,860 --> 00:59:15,960
Father!

832
00:59:19,559 --> 00:59:20,630
Father.

833
00:59:21,300 --> 00:59:22,329
Father.

834
00:59:23,030 --> 00:59:24,630
- Father. - Father!

835
00:59:26,230 --> 00:59:27,800
Did someone die around here?

836
00:59:28,769 --> 00:59:30,368
Why are you all crying?

837
00:59:30,369 --> 00:59:34,179
Father, I checked the final list of passengers from Baghdad just now.

838
00:59:34,380 --> 00:59:36,880
So? Are you disappointed...

839
00:59:37,250 --> 00:59:38,308
that I came back alive?

840
00:59:38,309 --> 00:59:40,679
Don't say it like that, Father!

841
00:59:40,880 --> 00:59:42,650
Because of you, we were all just...

842
00:59:43,119 --> 00:59:45,750
Good grief. You were all worried for nothing.

843
00:59:46,820 --> 00:59:49,260
Your father is yet to become a ghost.

844
00:59:54,059 --> 00:59:57,730
Your mom's face is what looks like a ghost.

845
01:00:04,670 --> 01:00:06,538
There was a change in his schedule due to business,

846
01:00:06,539 --> 01:00:08,380
so he had to arrive in Seoul earlier.

847
01:00:08,809 --> 01:00:12,210
We switched to another flight at the stopover, Abu Dhabi,

848
01:00:14,019 --> 01:00:15,820
so we were able to avoid this disaster.

849
01:00:17,090 --> 01:00:18,288
Great job.

850
01:00:18,289 --> 01:00:20,519
- Father. - Father.

851
01:00:26,090 --> 01:00:27,400
Father.

852
01:00:31,429 --> 01:00:32,929
What a relief, Father.

853
01:00:33,969 --> 01:00:36,500
I heard you suddenly had a business in Seoul.

854
01:00:36,940 --> 01:00:39,769
I don't know whose business it is, but I'd like to go bow to them.

855
01:00:40,809 --> 01:00:42,479
It's Youngjin Semiconductor.

856
01:00:42,480 --> 01:00:44,010
They're selling the business, right?

857
01:00:44,510 --> 01:00:46,050
I hear they will do it soon.

858
01:00:46,780 --> 01:00:48,750
I bought it today.

859
01:00:49,880 --> 01:00:51,348
Youngjin Semiconductor.

860
01:00:51,349 --> 01:00:52,848
- What? - What?

861
01:00:52,849 --> 01:00:54,789
Wait, weren't you going to give up on the semiconductor business?

862
01:00:56,059 --> 01:00:59,360
Father, you're going to jump in on this fight of whales?

863
01:00:59,530 --> 01:01:01,929
I'm going to make the shrimp bigger...

864
01:01:02,960 --> 01:01:05,369
so that the shrimp won't die in a fight between whales.

865
01:01:06,000 --> 01:01:08,900
- Father. - No matter how long it takes...

866
01:01:09,039 --> 01:01:10,969
or how much I have to invest,

867
01:01:13,409 --> 01:01:16,710
I will make this shrimp as big as a whale.

868
01:01:16,940 --> 01:01:18,578
But Father, right now, it's not...

869
01:01:18,579 --> 01:01:20,550
I just came back from my death.

870
01:01:22,119 --> 01:01:25,449
Do you think there is anything I'll be afraid of?

871
01:01:48,579 --> 01:01:49,780
(Pending Approval)

872
01:01:58,949 --> 01:02:03,019
I finally found out the answer to the quiz you asked, Grandpa.

873
01:02:04,230 --> 01:02:06,860
A way for a shrimp to beat the whales.

874
01:02:07,599 --> 01:02:09,429
It's to make the shrimp bigger.

875
01:02:09,829 --> 01:02:12,000
Then it won't die in the midst of a whales' fight.

876
01:02:13,130 --> 01:02:16,639
If you do not give up, time will be on the shrimp's side.

877
01:02:18,070 --> 01:02:20,170
The proposal of the buyout of Youngjin Semiconductor...

878
01:02:20,579 --> 01:02:22,340
ends at 5pm on the 29th.

879
01:02:23,909 --> 01:02:25,380
Once you see this note,

880
01:02:26,010 --> 01:02:29,119
I believe that you will change your flight.

881
01:02:35,420 --> 01:02:36,489
Chairman Jin.

882
01:02:39,429 --> 01:02:41,730
Are we stopping over at Abu Dhabi?

883
01:02:42,059 --> 01:02:43,130
Yes.

884
01:02:45,500 --> 01:02:48,269
Find the earliest flight to Seoul.

885
01:03:22,840 --> 01:03:25,940
Congratulations, Mr. President.

886
01:03:32,010 --> 01:03:33,780
During your presidency,

887
01:03:35,179 --> 01:03:37,789
please allow Soonyang to monopolize...

888
01:03:39,150 --> 01:03:40,590
the semiconductor business.

889
01:03:44,929 --> 01:03:46,289
Thank you.

890
01:03:57,570 --> 01:03:58,840
Just as you said,

891
01:03:59,570 --> 01:04:02,639
I handed over the fund for the presidential election myself.

892
01:04:07,750 --> 01:04:08,849
Why did you...

893
01:04:10,420 --> 01:04:11,989
tell me to fund...

894
01:04:14,420 --> 01:04:16,760
the second and third runners who aren't going to make it?

895
01:04:17,659 --> 01:04:19,558
Once the first place graduates,

896
01:04:19,559 --> 01:04:21,860
there will come a day for the 2nd and 3rd to win.

897
01:04:28,440 --> 01:04:29,440
By any chance,

898
01:04:31,869 --> 01:04:33,940
do you know what the future holds?

899
01:04:44,489 --> 01:04:47,289
You knew the single candidacy will fall under.

900
01:04:50,190 --> 01:04:52,889
You knew Roh Tae Woo would be elected.

901
01:04:56,260 --> 01:04:57,369
And...

902
01:05:04,070 --> 01:05:05,210
(I finally found out the answer to the quiz you asked, Grandpa.)

903
01:05:11,849 --> 01:05:13,809
you knew CAL 828 will blow up.

904
01:05:17,219 --> 01:05:18,949
You knew everything.

905
01:05:21,460 --> 01:05:22,489
Is that true?

906
01:05:26,030 --> 01:05:27,190
Answer me!

907
01:05:42,309 --> 01:05:43,579
I did know.

908
01:05:48,320 --> 01:05:49,480
Not the future,

909
01:05:50,949 --> 01:05:52,920
but I knew what was in your heart.

910
01:05:56,590 --> 01:05:59,889
There is no way for a shrimp to win against whales.

911
01:06:01,400 --> 01:06:03,329
You gave me that quiz...

912
01:06:04,070 --> 01:06:06,300
trying to grasp for straws because you knew...

913
01:06:06,500 --> 01:06:08,070
your new attempt seemed reckless.

914
01:06:11,070 --> 01:06:12,340
You weren't looking for an answer.

915
01:06:13,170 --> 01:06:15,110
You were looking for approval and support.

916
01:06:17,880 --> 01:06:19,409
All I knew was...

917
01:06:20,480 --> 01:06:22,079
how you felt in your heart.

918
01:06:35,159 --> 01:06:37,869
Why is he seeing him alone in the study?

919
01:06:38,969 --> 01:06:40,769
I mean, without Mr. Lee.

920
01:06:41,699 --> 01:06:44,309
- What's with Father? - Tell me about it.

921
01:06:44,909 --> 01:06:46,469
That rarely happens for us too.

922
01:06:49,079 --> 01:06:50,239
Young Ki.

923
01:06:55,579 --> 01:06:57,349
You got the answer,

924
01:06:59,489 --> 01:07:00,820
so you deserve the prize.

925
01:07:03,519 --> 01:07:04,730
How much do you want?

926
01:07:05,059 --> 01:07:06,559
I don't need money.

927
01:07:08,929 --> 01:07:11,199
Once I am old enough to use that money,

928
01:07:11,429 --> 01:07:13,070
its monetary value would have dropped.

929
01:07:16,170 --> 01:07:17,170
Is that so?

930
01:07:17,739 --> 01:07:18,809
I'd like land.

931
01:07:19,710 --> 01:07:22,909
A place with lots of plants and trees.

932
01:07:30,820 --> 01:07:33,019
I like this area, right here.

933
01:07:37,789 --> 01:07:41,629
That land was used to make pottery. It's useless.

934
01:07:41,630 --> 01:07:43,399
(Map of Seoul)

935
01:07:43,400 --> 01:07:44,868
(Gyeonggi Province, Seongnam, Bundang-dong)

936
01:07:44,869 --> 01:07:46,369
Do you want the land in Bundang that badly?

937
01:07:50,739 --> 01:07:52,340
Let's see.

938
01:07:53,809 --> 01:07:55,210
How does 160,000m sound?

939
01:07:55,739 --> 01:07:58,110
There is one more thing I'd like, Grandpa.

940
01:07:58,210 --> 01:08:00,380
I think I'm done paying you out.

941
01:08:05,219 --> 01:08:06,289
Then let's make it a deal.

942
01:08:14,159 --> 01:08:18,199
You need to have something that I do not have...

943
01:08:18,970 --> 01:08:20,270
for a deal to be made.

944
01:08:21,800 --> 01:08:23,840
Do you think there is anything I do not have?

945
01:08:24,640 --> 01:08:26,409
Because you can't buy this with money.

946
01:08:28,810 --> 01:08:32,949
I'll bring you something that the Soonyang family doesn't have.

947
01:08:35,979 --> 01:08:37,719
The acceptance letter to the most prestigious college,

948
01:08:37,720 --> 01:08:39,420
Seoul National University, School of Law.

949
01:08:50,029 --> 01:08:51,069
You're right.

950
01:08:53,000 --> 01:08:54,539
An acceptance letter, I cannot buy that.

951
01:08:56,869 --> 01:08:57,970
Can you do this?

952
01:09:02,010 --> 01:09:03,739
What can I give you in return?

953
01:09:10,250 --> 01:09:11,649
Gather round, everyone.

954
01:09:26,569 --> 01:09:27,600
Jeong Rae.

955
01:09:28,670 --> 01:09:29,699
Yes, Father.

956
01:09:30,170 --> 01:09:32,470
Starting with the family gathering this weekend,

957
01:09:33,010 --> 01:09:35,239
make sure you set out...

958
01:09:36,239 --> 01:09:38,350
enough utensils for Do Jun's family as well.

959
01:09:47,619 --> 01:09:48,819
Why won't you answer me?

960
01:09:49,659 --> 01:09:51,890
Every week?

961
01:09:52,590 --> 01:09:54,699
Do Jun here is my grandson.

962
01:09:56,460 --> 01:09:57,600
Do you understand now?

963
01:10:18,350 --> 01:10:19,420
Family.

964
01:10:22,789 --> 01:10:24,630
4-alpha was right.

965
01:10:26,090 --> 01:10:27,960
There must be a reason why I became this family.

966
01:10:30,460 --> 01:10:32,699
The reason why I became family with the Jins.

967
01:10:37,170 --> 01:10:38,239
Right here.

968
01:10:43,340 --> 01:10:44,810
One of these people...

969
01:10:50,279 --> 01:10:52,090
killed me.

970
01:11:11,210 --> 01:11:14,139
How do you feel about entering SNU's law program as the top?

971
01:11:14,140 --> 01:11:15,879
Tell us your secret.

972
01:11:15,880 --> 01:11:18,779
How did you get in as the top of the class?

973
01:11:18,880 --> 01:11:22,149
- Say something. - Please introduce yourself.

974
01:11:24,180 --> 01:11:25,189
Well.

975
01:11:26,390 --> 01:11:29,560
I'm sure you all know my name.

976
01:11:31,090 --> 01:11:32,859
So is this what you're looking for?

977
01:11:35,460 --> 01:11:38,170
Chairman Jin Yang Cheol's grandson,

978
01:11:39,600 --> 01:11:42,869
College of Law, the class of 1996. My name is Jin Do Jun.

979
01:11:43,970 --> 01:11:45,909
I was born as Jin Do Jun...

980
01:11:46,439 --> 01:11:48,680
not as spirit possession, time traveling,

981
01:11:49,380 --> 01:11:50,510
or reincarnation.

982
01:11:51,850 --> 01:11:54,979
This life is my opportunity.

983
01:11:55,319 --> 01:11:59,390
(Reborn Rich)

984
01:12:29,619 --> 01:12:31,289
Play. Have fun.

985
01:12:31,689 --> 01:12:34,019
Go on group blind dates, regular blind dates,

986
01:12:34,020 --> 01:12:35,788
casual dates, and go out with someone.

987
01:12:35,789 --> 01:12:37,020
We've met before, right?

988
01:12:37,960 --> 01:12:39,489
Did you meet her? When?

989
01:12:40,090 --> 01:12:41,159
In 20 years' time.

990
01:12:41,229 --> 01:12:42,659
Do Jun, you're back!

991
01:12:44,060 --> 01:12:46,828
Why does Father play favorites with the youngest, Do Jun?

992
01:12:46,829 --> 01:12:49,170
Do Jun has exchanged the money in the account into dollars.

993
01:12:49,439 --> 01:12:51,409
I'd like to invest in companies in the US.

994
01:12:51,539 --> 01:12:54,038
Never bet on things that you aren't sure about.

995
01:12:54,039 --> 01:12:55,409
I have a lot of money, Mr. Oh.

996
01:12:55,640 --> 01:12:56,739
There is a problem.

997
01:12:56,840 --> 01:12:58,249
Just why?

998
01:12:58,250 --> 01:12:59,710
It's a foreign investment company.

999
01:13:00,350 --> 01:13:01,419
Mr. Chairman...

1000
01:13:01,420 --> 01:13:05,318
would like to pass Soonyang down to someone who is like him.

1001
01:13:05,319 --> 01:13:07,149
Do you simply have good discernment?

1002
01:13:07,689 --> 01:13:09,220
Or are you just lucky?

1003
01:13:36,949 --> 01:13:40,119
(Reborn Rich)
